variables.selected_prompt_text:
Decompose the problem into a maximum of two highly efficient subproblems for other agents. Each helper must be assigned a distinct, critical component of the solution (e.g., one for algorithmic logic and one for constraint handling). Ensure the decomposition is lean to avoid exceeding orchestration limits. Use plain text only inside helper instructions. Do not use markdown, code fences, or LaTeX-style backslashes.

Return exactly one JSON object in this format:
{
  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "optional string",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "plain-text subproblem for the first helper"
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "how the parent should combine the child results"
}
